Day 29 – Linear Regression Theory

Today I started learning Linear Regression, one of the most fundamental algorithms in Machine Learning.

What is Linear Regression?

Linear Regression is used to model the relationship between:

Independent variable (X)

Dependent variable (Y)


It finds the best fit line:

y = mx + b

Where:

m = slope

b = intercept



---

Goal of Linear Regression

Find the best line that minimizes the error between predicted and actual values.

This is done using:

Residuals (Errors)

Least Squares Method



